{"key":"processedPost-8902338","value":{"id":8902338,"first":8901028,"last":8906027,"when":1220991223,"utime":"09/09/08 11:13 PM","content":"There's a section on lighting at the bottom of the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">BRF Tek page</a> on my website.&nbsp; We've learned a LOT about growing mushrooms, as well as lighting in the last 20 years.&nbsp; Disregard what you read about a 15 watt bulb, especially if it's talking about incandescent.&nbsp; They suck for performance.&nbsp; <br /><br />Fluorescent lighting is perfect for mushrooms.&nbsp; The brighter the better, just don't get the tube so close the heat causes drying.&nbsp; The tubes you want will be labeled 'cool white' for 5,000 Kelvin, but even better is 'natural daylight' which will have a color temperature of 6,500 Kelvin and will help produce much better pinsets.<br />RR","title":"Re: just a few growing questions for a noob.... before i start..","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}